# TypeScript Error Handling

## Exception Guidelines
- ✅ Exception messages must always be constant strings
  ```typescript
  // Good
  throw new BaseException('Failed to download file')
  
  // Bad
  throw new BaseException(`Failed downloading file ${fileId}`)
  ```
- ✅ Use `error` as the variable name in catch blocks with implicit `unknown` type
- ✅ Don't specify explicit types in catch blocks
- ✅ REST service exceptions should extend NestJS's `HttpException`
- ❌ Avoid try-catch solely for naive error logging
- ✅ Implement "fast fail" approach - throw exceptions early

## Error Context
- ✅ Always provide meaningful context in error messages
- ✅ Include relevant IDs and state information in error context
- ✅ Log failures when exceptions aren't thrown

> **For NestJS/REST APIs**: See [NestJS-Specific Exception Handling](nest-guidelines.mdc#error-handling) for HTTP exceptions and global filters.
